DuplicateFilesChecker -
To check for duplicate files in the baseDir. Initialize with path String.
	:checkDuplicates(FileC) - Called from constructor automatically.
	:displayDistinct() - Prints the names of all the files in the baseDir & subdirectories to the standard out.
	:displayDuplicates() - Prints the names of duplicaet files in the baseDir & subdirectories to the standard out, grouped.
	:indexInDuplicates(FileC) - Example of bad program design.

FileC - 
Container. Extends java.io.File, compares by filename instead of path.

DuplicateFiles -
Container with an ArrayList<File> to store files with same name.